Holt Spalding
Random Walk Experiment: Sutton & Barto Exercise 7.2
Date: 10/26/18

Description: 
    In the provided python file is a short experiment showcasing the performance differences
    between online and offline n-step TD methods on a random walk task. Details of the problem 
    and  the experiment are aviable in the provided paper. 

Usage:
    If you would like to run your own experiment, simply run file and the results will be 
    saved as pngs to your current working directory. You can change the number of runs of the 
    experiment and the number of episodes per run by changing the parameters of the call
    to experiment() at the bottom of the file. This was not designed to be user-friendly,
    only to produce the graphs which feature in the corresponding paper. 


